.TH mlib_SignalMulSShift_S16_Sat 3MLIB "2 Mar 2007" "SunOS 5.11" "mediaLib Library Functions"
.SH NAME
mlib_SignalMulSShift_S16_Sat, mlib_SignalMulSShift_S16S_Sat \- multiplication by a scalar with shifting
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
cc [ \fIflag\fR... ] \fIfile\fR... \fB-lmlib\fR [ \fIlibrary\fR... ]
#include <mlib.h>

\fBmlib_status\fR \fBmlib_SignalMulSShift_S16_Sat\fR(\fBmlib_s16 *\fR\fIsrcdst\fR,
     \fBconst mlib_s16 *\fR\fIc\fR, \fBmlib_s32\fR \fIshift\fR, \fBmlib_s32\fR \fIn\fR);
.fi

.LP
.nf
\fBmlib_status\fR \fBmlib_SignalMulSShift_S16S_Sat\fR(\fBmlib_s16 *\fR\fIsrcdst\fR,
     \fBconst mlib_s16 *\fR\fIc\fR, \fBmlib_s32\fR \fIshift\fR, \fBmlib_s32\fR \fIn\fR);
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
Each of these functions performs multiplication by a scalar with shifting.
.SH PARAMETERS
.sp
.LP
Each of the functions takes the following arguments:
.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fB\fIsrcdst\fR\fR
.ad
.RS 10n
.rt  
Source and destination signal array.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fB\fIc\fR\fR
.ad
.RS 10n
.rt  
Scaling factor. The scaling factor is in Q15 format. In the stereo version; c[0] contains the scaling factor for channel 0, and c[1] holds the scaling factor for channel 1.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fB\fIshift\fR\fR
.ad
.RS 10n
.rt  
Left shifting factor.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fB\fIn\fR\fR
.ad
.RS 10n
.rt  
Number of samples in the input signal arrays.
.RE

.SH RETURN VALUES
.sp
.LP
Each of the functions returns \fBMLIB_SUCCESS\fR if successful. Otherwise it returns \fBMLIB_FAILURE\fR.
